# Authorship (hard rule)

All work in this repository is attributed to **Sirius T.Bontea** `<sirius.bontea@protonmail.com>`.

## Required

- **Git commits** — author must be `Sirius T.Bontea <sirius.bontea@protonmail.com>`. Use conventional commit messages; no AI attribution in subject or body.
- **Code** — do not add file headers, comments, or metadata crediting an AI, assistant, model, or tool as author or co-author.
- **Docs & packaging** — README, LICENSE, `package.json`, `AGENTS.md`, and similar files must not list AI systems as authors or contributors.

## Forbidden

- `Co-authored-by:` trailers (or any trailer) naming an AI, assistant, Cursor, Grok, Copilot, etc.
- Phrases like "generated by", "written with AI", "assisted by", or model names in commit messages, code comments, or user-facing docs.
- Adding a second human or bot author without explicit instruction from Sirius T.Bontea.

## When implementing

- Write code and commits as human-authored work under the name above.
- If a template or tool injects authorship metadata, remove or override it before finishing.
- Do not suggest or add "AI helped build this" disclaimers to the product UI or README unless explicitly requested.
